
********** GIT & GIT HUB *************

Install git ( https://git-scm.com/install/windows )

git --version ( To check the version of git )

Basic Linux Commands:

touch filename

touch filename1 filename2 filename3 ( TO create multiple files )

cat filename ( To view the content in the file )

vi / vim / nano ( To edit the content in the file )

mv filename newfilename ( To replace the filename )

mkdir dirname

mkdir dirnmae1 dirname2 dirname3 ( TO create multiple directories )

rm -rf filename or dirname ( To remove file or directory with recursively & forcefully )

ls ( list files )

ll ( long list )

ls -lrth ( To open all the files with all details )

ls -la ( To view include all hidden files )

cd /home ( To change the directory )

cd .. ( To comeback from the present directory a step back )

pwd ( To check present working directory )

clear ( To clear the screen )

*****************************************************************************************

Repository ( 

git init ( To initalize the empty repo )

git config --global user.name "username" ( To configure the user details )

git config --global user.email "test.com"

git status ( To check the status )

git add filename ( To move the file from workspace to staging )
 
git status 

By defauly files will be in workspace which indicates the files in RED colour

git commit -m "msg" filename ( Will move from staging to local repo )

git status

Files will be change from RED to green ( i.e files moved from workspace to staging )

git log ( To check the commit details of a user who modified )

q ( To come out from )

git show ( commit ID ) to check the commit changes

git add . ( To move all the files from workspace to staging in a single go )

git commit -m "message" ( If you don't give the file name all the files will be commited )

git show ( To see the content in the files )

**********************************************************************************************

GIT-HUB

Create a github account ( https://github.com/signup?source=login )

Create a Repository in ur github & copy the URL

git clone ( github repository URL )

ls

cd ( Repository )

ll

touch filename

git status

git add filname

git status

git commit -m "message"

git log

git push

You will see the pop-up of signin with browser

Rrefresh the repository to see the files in web portal

If you do any changes in the file again you need to add & commit then push again.

If you delete the file you can see it in the git status as deleted - You can commit to delete from cloud repo.

*****************************************************************************
GIT File:

touch Prasad

git add Prasad

git commit -m "Created a file and uploaded the latest version on code" Prasad

git push

Delete:

rm -rf Prasad

git status

git commit -m "File deleted as we have some miscommunication" Prasad

git push ( To delete in centralized repo )

GIT Branch:
 
git branch ( To list all the branches )
 
git branch name

git checkout name

git merge name

git push URL ( Branch Name )

git push origin branch name ( Instead of URL to push to main branch )

git branch -d ( Branch Name ) 

git branch -D ( Branch Name ) to delete forcefully

git push origin -d ( Branch Name )

git cherry-pick (CID)

@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@

git branch
git branch testing
git checkout testing
ls
cd Git/
ls
touch testfile2 testfile3
git status
git add . && git commit -m "commiting for my branch files" testfile2 testfile3
git log
ls
vi testfile1
git status
git add testfile1
git commit -m "Added few changes in my testfile1" testfile1
git push origin testing
git checkout main
git merge testing

git branch -r 

git checkout branchname

@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@

GIT Amend:

git commit -- amend -m "For change the commit message" ( To change the commit message for only latest commit log )

git commit --amend -m "For change the commit message" -m "Ticket ID" 

@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@

GIT Filtering:

git log -2 ( Change the number to see only mentioned number of logs )

git log --oneline ( To see all the logs in oneline )

git show Log ID ( To see the complete content in the log )

git log --oneline -2 ( To see the mentioned number of logs in oneline )

git log --author "Prasad" ( To see the logs of the author or user )

git log --since="2025-10-28" or git log --since="December 18 2025"

git config --list ( To list modifications of user information list )

@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@

Alias: To chnage the shortcuts of the commands

git config --global alias.l "log"

git config --global alias.s "status"

git config --global --unset alias.s ( To remove the status shortcuts )

@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@
To commit directly without adding the file to staging

Workspace > Staging > Local Repo 

The below process is only for workspace > Local Repo ( But first commit should follow the 3 steps }

Only for modified files

git commit -am "message"

EX: touch prasad
git commit -m "message" ( Will not commit )

git add prasad && git commit -m "message" prasad

Modified: vi prasad
git commit -m "message" prasad ( Now you can commit directly without adding to staging )

@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@

File Backward:

git reset HEAD filename (Staging to workspace)

git reset --soft (CID) n-1 (Local repo to staging)

git reset --mixed (CID) n-1 (Local repo to workspace)

@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@@

GIT TAG:

git tag

git tag (Tag Name) CID

git checkout (Tag Name) CID

git tag -d (Tag Name) CID

git push origin (Tag Name) (You can see the TAG in ur github web to check and download)

git push origin -d (Tag Name) 

